            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">Student ID</p>
              <p class="font-semibold">102543246</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">Subject</p>
              <p class="font-semibold">WEB 322</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">Email</p>
              <p class="font-semibold">
                <a class="link" href="mailto:kcjat@myseneca.ca">kcjat@myseneca.ca</a>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Project tech stack -->
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h2 class="card-title">Technologies Used</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li><span class="font-semibold">Node.js + Express</span> for server-side routing and middleware.</li>
            <li><span class="font-semibold">EJS</span> templating to render dynamic pages from JSON data.</li>
            <li><span class="font-semibold">Tailwind CSS</span> with <span class="font-semibold">DaisyUI</span> components for fast, responsive UI.</li>
            <li><span class="font-semibold">JSON data</span> source (<code>data/projects.json</code>) for sectors/projects.</li>
            <li><span class="font-semibold">Vercel</span> for hosting the Express app with GitHub integration.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why environment & climate matter -->
    <section class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">Why Focus on Environment & Climate?</h2>
        <p>
          Climate change is not an abstract topic—it influences food security, energy costs,
          infrastructure resilience, and day-to-day health. Software can help by making data
          easy to explore, revealing trade-offs, and highlighting solutions that scale.
          This project organizes information by sector (Agriculture, Electricity, Transportation)
          so people can quickly navigate real actions and impacts.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Personal perspective -->
    <section class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">My Perspective</h2>
        <p>
          In my view, today’s climatic conditions show a clear pattern—hotter summers, sudden
          storms, and unpredictable seasons. Even small inefficiencies compound into major
          problems when multiplied across cities and supply chains. I believe developers have a
          responsibility to build tools that are transparent, practical, and respectful of
          real-world constraints. This assignment is a small step toward presenting climate
          information in a way that motivates action rather than anxiety.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Acknowledgment -->
    <section class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">Acknowledgment</h2>
        <p>
          I would like to thank <span class="font-semibold">Professor Rohit Gaur</span> for
          guidance and support throughout this project. The feedback on routing structure,
          view composition, and deployment expectations helped me keep the solution clean,
          consistent, and aligned with WEB322 outcomes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
